import LevyStochCalc.BSDEJ.Definition
import LevyStochCalc.Brownian.MultidimIto

/-!
# Layer 3a: Jacod-Yor martingale representation for `(W, √Ď)`

Every L¬≤-martingale on the filtration generated by Brownian motion `W` and
a Poisson random measure `N` admits a unique two-source predictable
representation:

  `M_t = M_0 + ‚ąę_0^t Z_s ¬∑ dW_s + ‚ąę_0^t ‚ąę_E U_s(e) √Ď(ds, de)`

with `Z ‚ąą H¬≤(dt ‚äó dP; ‚ĄĚ^d)` and `U ‚ąą H¬≤(dt ‚äó dP ‚äó dőĹ; ‚ĄĚ)`.

## Source

* Jacod, J. "Multivariate point processes: predictable projection,
  Radon-Nikodym derivatives, representation of martingales",
  Z. Wahrsch. Verw. Gebiete 31(3), 1975, pp 235‚Äď253.
* Jacod‚ÄďShiryaev, *Limit Theorems for Stochastic Processes*, 2nd ed.,
  Springer 2003, Theorem III.4.34.

## Status (2026-05-26, Tier 1 #13 axiom ‚Üí narrower-axiom decomposition)

Previously a single Tier 1 axiom `jacodYor_representation_axiom`. Now
**decomposed** into two strictly narrower Tier 1 axioms:

* `jacodYor_PRP_martingale_axiom` (Tier 1 #13a) ‚ÄĒ the LITERAL content of
  Jacod-Shiryaev III.4.34: predictable representation property for c√†dl√†g
  L¬≤ (W, N)-martingales. This is the deep mathematical content (the
  predictable-projection / chaos-decomposition machinery of Jacod 1976).
* `condExp_to_PRP_martingale_form_axiom` (Tier 1 #13b) ‚ÄĒ the standard
  classical bridge: the c√†dl√†g L¬≤ modification of the conditional-
  expectation martingale `M_t := E[őĺ | F_t]` is a martingale on the
  joint (W, N) right-continuous filtration with `M_0 = E[őĺ]` a.s.
  (Blumenthal-flavor 0-1 triviality of F_0) and `M_T = őĺ` a.s. (since
  őĺ is F_T-measurable). This is **strictly narrower** because each
  conjunct is a known classical theorem with a separate citation
  (Karatzas-Shreve I.3.13 for Doob L¬≤ c√†dl√†g regularization; K-S 2.7.17
  for Blumenthal 0-1; `MeasureTheory.condExp_of_stronglyMeasurable` is
  already in Mathlib).

The previous single `jacodYor_representation_axiom` is now **derived as a
theorem** from #13a + #13b. The downstream-facing
`jacodYor_representation` theorem is unchanged (still a thin forwarder,
now over the derived theorem rather than over the previously-monolithic
axiom).

**Signature: FULLY PINNED** (both Brownian and compensated-Poisson integrals).
The conclusion uses `MultidimBrownianMotion.stochasticIntegral W Z ...`
and `Compensated.stochasticIntegral N U ...` as the literal RHS terms,
with the per-component progressive-measurability + L¬≤ hypotheses bundled
as existential witnesses. This means a trivial `Z = 0, U = 0` witness no
longer works.

**Replacement plan**:
* `jacodYor_PRP_martingale_axiom` ‚Üí theorem when Mathlib gains chaos
  decomposition / predictable projection for the (W, N) filtration
  (waits on Tier 1 #5 + #6 + extensive PRP infrastructure).
* `condExp_to_PRP_martingale_form_axiom` ‚Üí theorem when Mathlib gains
  (i) Doob L¬≤ c√†dl√†g modification for right-continuous filtrations
  (Karatzas-Shreve I.3.13), (ii) Blumenthal-style 0-1 / F_0 triviality
  for the joint (W, N) filtration (K-S 2.7.17 + analog for Poisson
  random measures). Both are well-defined Mathlib targets independent
  of the PRP work.
-/

open MeasureTheory ProbabilityTheory
open scoped NNReal ENNReal

namespace LevyStochCalc.BSDEJ.MartingaleRepresentation

universe u v

variable {ő© : Type u} [MeasurableSpace ő©]
variable {E : Type v} [MeasurableSpace E]

/-- Abbreviation for the joint right-continuous (W, N) filtration appearing
in every statement below. Locally bound to keep statements legible. -/
noncomputable abbrev jointFiltration
    {P : Measure ő©} [IsProbabilityMeasure P]
    {őĹ : Measure E} [SigmaFinite őĹ]
    {d : ‚Ąē}
    (W : LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion P d)
    (N : LevyStochCalc.Poisson.PoissonRandomMeasure P őĹ) :
    MeasureTheory.Filtration ‚ĄĚ ‚ÄĻMeasurableSpace ő©‚Äļ :=
  ((‚®Ü i : Fin d, LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Martingale.naturalFiltration (W.W i))
    ‚äĒ LevyStochCalc.Poisson.naturalFiltration N).rightCont

/-- **Predictable representation property (PRP) for c√†dl√†g L¬≤ (W, N)-martingales
‚ÄĒ Jacod-Shiryaev III.4.34, Tier 1 cited axiom #13a.**

For every L¬≤-bounded c√†dl√†g martingale `M` on the joint right-continuous
filtration `‚ĄĪ = ((‚®Ü i, ŌÉ(W_i)) ‚äĒ ŌÉ(N)).rightCont`, there exist
predictable square-integrable integrands `Z, U` such that

  `M_t = M_0 + ‚ąę_0^t Z_s ¬∑ dW_s + ‚ąę_0^t ‚ąę_E U_s(e) √Ď(ds, de)  a.s.`

at every `t ‚ąą [0, T]`.

This is the LITERAL statement of Jacod-Shiryaev III.4.34 (or equivalently
Jacod 1976 Theorem 3.75). It is the **deep mathematical content** of the
two-source martingale representation; the conditional-expectation
construction `M_t := E[őĺ | ‚ĄĪ_t]` for a generic L¬≤ random variable `őĺ`
appears in the next axiom `condExp_to_PRP_martingale_form_axiom` and is
ELEMENTARY classical bookkeeping by comparison.

**Reference**: Jacod, J. "Multivariate point processes: predictable
projection, Radon-Nikodym derivatives, representation of martingales",
Z. Wahrsch. Verw. Gebiete 31(3), 1975, pp 235-253; Jacod-Shiryaev,
*Limit Theorems for Stochastic Processes*, 2nd ed., Springer 2003,
**Theorem III.4.34**. The cited theorem in Jacod-Shiryaev is stated in
EXACTLY the martingale-input form of this axiom. -/
axiom jacodYor_PRP_martingale_axiom
    {P : Measure ő©} [IsProbabilityMeasure P]
    {őĹ : Measure E} [SigmaFinite őĹ]
    {d : ‚Ąē}
    (W : LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion P d)
    (N : LevyStochCalc.Poisson.PoissonRandomMeasure P őĹ)
    (T : ‚ĄĚ) (_hT : 0 < T)
    -- The c√†dl√†g L¬≤-bounded martingale input.
    (M : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
    (_h_M_mart : MeasureTheory.Martingale M (jointFiltration W N) P)
    (_h_M_sq_int : ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, (‚ÄĖM T ŌČ‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāP < ‚ä§)
    (_h_M_cadlag : ‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ,
      Filter.Tendsto (fun s => M s ŌČ) (nhdsWithin t (Set.Ioi t)) (nhds (M t ŌČ))
        ‚ąß ‚ąÉ L : ‚ĄĚ,
            Filter.Tendsto (fun s => M s ŌČ) (nhdsWithin t (Set.Iio t)) (nhds L)) :
    -- Same (Z, U) existential witnesses as `jacodYor_representation_axiom`.
    ‚ąÉ (Z : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí (Fin d ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ))
      (h_Z_meas : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d,
        Measurable (Function.uncurry (fun ŌČ s => Z s ŌČ i)))
      (h_Z_progMeas : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ,
        @MeasureTheory.StronglyMeasurable (ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ) ‚ĄĚ _
          (@Prod.instMeasurableSpace ő© ‚ĄĚ
            ((LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Martingale.naturalFiltration (W.W i)).seq t)
            inferInstance)
          (fun p : ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ => Z p.2 p.1 i))
      (h_Z_sq_int : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d, ‚ąÄ T' : ‚ĄĚ, 0 < T' ‚Üí
        ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, ‚ąę‚ĀĽ s in Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T',
          (‚ÄĖZ s ŌČ i‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāvolume ‚ąāP < ‚ä§)
      (U : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí E ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
      (h_U_meas : Measurable
        (fun (p : ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó E) =>
          (fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) p.1 p.2.1 p.2.2))
      (h_U_progMeas : ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ,
        @MeasureTheory.StronglyMeasurable (ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó E) ‚ĄĚ _
          (@Prod.instMeasurableSpace ő© (‚ĄĚ √ó E)
            ((LevyStochCalc.Poisson.naturalFiltration N).seq t)
            inferInstance)
          (fun p : ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó E => (fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) p.1 p.2.1 p.2.2))
      (h_U_sq : ‚ąÄ T' : ‚ĄĚ, 0 < T' ‚Üí
        ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, ‚ąę‚ĀĽ s in Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T', ‚ąę‚ĀĽ e,
          (‚ÄĖ(fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) ŌČ s e‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2
            ‚ąāőĹ ‚ąāvolume ‚ąāP < ‚ä§),
      (‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP, M T ŌČ = M 0 ŌČ
        + LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion.stochasticIntegral
            W Z h_Z_meas h_Z_progMeas h_Z_sq_int T ŌČ
        + LevyStochCalc.Poisson.Compensated.stochasticIntegral N
            (fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) h_U_meas h_U_progMeas h_U_sq T ŌČ)

/-- **Conditional-expectation martingale c√†dl√†g modification + endpoint
identification ‚ÄĒ Tier 1 cited axiom #13b.**

For every L¬≤ random variable `őĺ : ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ` that is `‚ĄĪ_T`-measurable on the
joint right-continuous (W, N) filtration, there exists a c√†dl√†g
L¬≤-bounded `‚ĄĪ`-martingale `M` with `M_0 = ‚ąę őĺ ‚ąāP` a.s. (i.e. `M_0` is
the deterministic expectation, NOT just `E[őĺ | ‚ĄĪ_0]`) and `M_T = őĺ`
a.s.

This packages THREE standard classical results:

1. **Doob L¬≤ c√†dl√†g regularization** (Karatzas-Shreve, *Brownian Motion
   and Stochastic Calculus*, Springer 1991, **Theorem I.3.13**): for a
   right-continuous filtration, every L¬Ļ martingale admits a c√†dl√†g
   modification.
2. **Blumenthal 0-1 law for the joint (W, N) filtration** (Karatzas-
   Shreve **Theorem 2.7.17** for the Brownian factor; analog for
   Poisson random measures via It√ī-Nisio / Applebaum 2.3.7): the right-
   continuous augmentation `‚ĄĪ_0+` is P-trivial, hence
   `ūĚĒľ[őĺ | ‚ĄĪ_0] = ‚ąę őĺ ‚ąāP` a.s.
3. **Conditional-expectation reproducibility** (Mathlib's
   `MeasureTheory.condExp_of_stronglyMeasurable`): `ūĚĒľ[őĺ | ‚ĄĪ_T] = őĺ`
   a.s. when őĺ is ‚ĄĪ_T-measurable and integrable.

The bundle is strictly narrower than `jacodYor_representation_axiom`:
no chaos decomposition / predictable projection is required, only
classical martingale + filtration machinery. Each of items 1, 2, 3
above has independent Mathlib activity (Doob regularization is on the
roadmap, Blumenthal-for-BM gets axiom-replaced when BM lands, condExp
is already there). When all three are usable in Mathlib, this axiom
collapses to a 3-line composite.

**Reference**: Karatzas-Shreve **Theorem I.3.13** (Doob L¬≤ c√†dl√†g
regularization); Karatzas-Shreve **Theorem 2.7.17** (Blumenthal 0-1
for Brownian); Mathlib's `MeasureTheory.condExp_of_stronglyMeasurable`
(condExp reproducibility ‚ÄĒ not citable, library lemma). -/
axiom condExp_to_PRP_martingale_form_axiom
    {P : Measure ő©} [IsProbabilityMeasure P]
    {őĹ : Measure E} [SigmaFinite őĹ]
    {d : ‚Ąē}
    (W : LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion P d)
    (N : LevyStochCalc.Poisson.PoissonRandomMeasure P őĹ)
    (T : ‚ĄĚ) (_hT : 0 < T)
    (őĺ : ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
    (_h_meas : @MeasureTheory.StronglyMeasurable ő© ‚ĄĚ _
      ((jointFiltration W N).seq T) őĺ)
    (_h_sq_int : ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, (‚ÄĖőĺ ŌČ‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāP < ‚ä§) :
    ‚ąÉ (M : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ),
      MeasureTheory.Martingale M (jointFiltration W N) P
      ‚ąß (‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, (‚ÄĖM T ŌČ‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāP < ‚ä§)
      ‚ąß (‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ,
          Filter.Tendsto (fun s => M s ŌČ)
            (nhdsWithin t (Set.Ioi t)) (nhds (M t ŌČ))
            ‚ąß ‚ąÉ L : ‚ĄĚ,
                Filter.Tendsto (fun s => M s ŌČ)
                  (nhdsWithin t (Set.Iio t)) (nhds L))
      ‚ąß (‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP, M 0 ŌČ = (‚ąę ŌČ', őĺ ŌČ' ‚ąāP))
      ‚ąß (‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP, M T ŌČ = őĺ ŌČ)

/-- **Jacod-Yor martingale representation (Jacod 1976), L¬≤ random-variable
form ‚ÄĒ DERIVED THEOREM (formerly Tier 1 axiom #13).**

Every square-integrable `‚ĄĪ_T`-measurable random variable `őĺ` admits a
representation

  `őĺ = ūĚĒľ[őĺ] + ‚ąę_0^T Z_s ¬∑ dW_s + ‚ąę_0^T ‚ąę_E U_s(e) √Ď(ds, de)  a.s.`

with predictable square-integrable integrands `Z, U`.

**Status (2026-05-26)**: this was previously the single Tier 1 axiom
`jacodYor_representation_axiom`. It is now derived from the two
narrower Tier 1 axioms:

* `jacodYor_PRP_martingale_axiom` (#13a ‚ÄĒ the deep PRP content)
* `condExp_to_PRP_martingale_form_axiom` (#13b ‚ÄĒ the classical bridge)

The derivation is a straightforward composition:

1. By #13b, build a c√†dl√†g L¬≤ martingale `M` with `M_0 = E[őĺ]` a.s.
   and `M_T = őĺ` a.s.
2. By #13a applied to `M`, get `(Z, U)` such that
   `M_T = M_0 + ‚ąęZ dW + ‚ąęU d√Ď` a.s.
3. Combine: `őĺ = M_T = M_0 + ‚ąęZ dW + ‚ąęU d√Ď = E[őĺ] + ‚ąęZ dW + ‚ąęU d√Ď` a.s. -/
theorem jacodYor_representation_axiom
    {P : Measure ő©} [IsProbabilityMeasure P]
    {őĹ : Measure E} [SigmaFinite őĹ]
    {d : ‚Ąē}
    (W : LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion P d)
    (N : LevyStochCalc.Poisson.PoissonRandomMeasure P őĹ)
    (T : ‚ĄĚ) (_hT : 0 < T)
    (őĺ : ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
    (h_meas : @MeasureTheory.StronglyMeasurable ő© ‚ĄĚ _
      ((jointFiltration W N).seq T) őĺ)
    (h_sq_int : ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, (‚ÄĖőĺ ŌČ‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāP < ‚ä§) :
    ‚ąÉ (Z : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí (Fin d ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ))
      (h_Z_meas : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d,
        Measurable (Function.uncurry (fun ŌČ s => Z s ŌČ i)))
      (h_Z_progMeas : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ,
        @MeasureTheory.StronglyMeasurable (ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ) ‚ĄĚ _
          (@Prod.instMeasurableSpace ő© ‚ĄĚ
            ((LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Martingale.naturalFiltration (W.W i)).seq t)
            inferInstance)
          (fun p : ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ => Z p.2 p.1 i))
      (h_Z_sq_int : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d, ‚ąÄ T' : ‚ĄĚ, 0 < T' ‚Üí
        ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, ‚ąę‚ĀĽ s in Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T',
          (‚ÄĖZ s ŌČ i‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāvolume ‚ąāP < ‚ä§)
      (U : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí E ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
      (h_U_meas : Measurable
        (fun (p : ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó E) =>
          (fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) p.1 p.2.1 p.2.2))
      (h_U_progMeas : ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ,
        @MeasureTheory.StronglyMeasurable (ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó E) ‚ĄĚ _
          (@Prod.instMeasurableSpace ő© (‚ĄĚ √ó E)
            ((LevyStochCalc.Poisson.naturalFiltration N).seq t)
            inferInstance)
          (fun p : ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó E => (fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) p.1 p.2.1 p.2.2))
      (h_U_sq : ‚ąÄ T' : ‚ĄĚ, 0 < T' ‚Üí
        ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, ‚ąę‚ĀĽ s in Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T', ‚ąę‚ĀĽ e,
          (‚ÄĖ(fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) ŌČ s e‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2
            ‚ąāőĹ ‚ąāvolume ‚ąāP < ‚ä§),
      (‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP, őĺ ŌČ = (‚ąę ŌČ', őĺ ŌČ' ‚ąāP)
        + LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion.stochasticIntegral
            W Z h_Z_meas h_Z_progMeas h_Z_sq_int T ŌČ
        + LevyStochCalc.Poisson.Compensated.stochasticIntegral N
            (fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) h_U_meas h_U_progMeas h_U_sq T ŌČ) := by
  -- Step 1: Apply #13b to build the c√†dl√†g L¬≤ martingale M = E[őĺ | ‚ĄĪ_¬∑].
  obtain ‚ü®M, h_M_mart, h_M_sq_int, h_M_cadlag, h_M0_eq, h_MT_eq‚ü© :=
    condExp_to_PRP_martingale_form_axiom W N T _hT őĺ h_meas h_sq_int
  -- Step 2: Apply #13a (PRP for c√†dl√†g L¬≤ (W, N)-martingales) to M.
  obtain ‚ü®Z, h_Z_meas, h_Z_progMeas, h_Z_sq_int,
          U, h_U_meas, h_U_progMeas, h_U_sq, h_repr‚ü© :=
    jacodYor_PRP_martingale_axiom W N T _hT M h_M_mart h_M_sq_int h_M_cadlag
  -- Step 3: Package the witnesses + combine the three a.s. equalities.
  refine ‚ü®Z, h_Z_meas, h_Z_progMeas, h_Z_sq_int,
          U, h_U_meas, h_U_progMeas, h_U_sq, ?_‚ü©
  filter_upwards [h_M0_eq, h_MT_eq, h_repr] with ŌČ hM0 hMT hRepr
  -- őĺ ŌČ = M T ŌČ  (from h_MT_eq)
  --     = M 0 ŌČ + ‚ąęZ dW + ‚ąęU d√Ď  (from h_repr)
  --     = E[őĺ] + ‚ąęZ dW + ‚ąęU d√Ď  (from h_M0_eq)
  rw [‚Üź hMT, hRepr, hM0]

/-- **Jacod-Yor martingale representation (Jacod 1976) ‚ÄĒ forwarding theorem.**

Thin forwarder over the derived theorem `jacodYor_representation_axiom`
(formerly Tier 1 axiom #13; as of 2026-05-26 derived from the narrower
Tier 1 axioms #13a `jacodYor_PRP_martingale_axiom` + #13b
`condExp_to_PRP_martingale_form_axiom`).

Stating this conclusion as a `theorem` here keeps every downstream caller
stable while making the dependency on Jacod 1976 explicit via the
underlying narrower axiom pair. -/
theorem jacodYor_representation
    {P : Measure ő©} [IsProbabilityMeasure P]
    {őĹ : Measure E} [SigmaFinite őĹ]
    {d : ‚Ąē}
    (W : LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion P d)
    (N : LevyStochCalc.Poisson.PoissonRandomMeasure P őĹ)
    (T : ‚ĄĚ) (_hT : 0 < T)
    (őĺ : ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
    -- őĺ is ‚ĄĪ_T-measurable, where ‚ĄĪ_T = (joint natural filtration of W, N).seq T.
    -- Per Jacod 1976: martingale representation REQUIRES őĺ to be measurable
    -- wrt the filtration at the endpoint T (otherwise őĺ depends on future
    -- information beyond T, and no (Z, U) integrals up to T can represent it).
    -- P4 M fix (red-team 2nd audit 2026-05-23): strengthened from bare
    -- `Measurable őĺ` (Borel) to `StronglyMeasurable[‚ĄĪ_T] őĺ`.
    (_h_meas : @MeasureTheory.StronglyMeasurable ő© ‚ĄĚ _
      (((‚®Ü i : Fin d, LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Martingale.naturalFiltration (W.W i))
        ‚äĒ LevyStochCalc.Poisson.naturalFiltration N).rightCont.seq T)
      őĺ)
    (_h_sq_int : ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, (‚ÄĖőĺ ŌČ‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāP < ‚ä§) :
    -- Existence of predictable square-integrable (Z, U) with the
    -- progressively-measurable hypotheses needed by the multidim
    -- Brownian It√ī integral, such that őĺ equals its mean plus the
    -- canonical Brownian It√ī integral of Z plus the canonical
    -- compensated-Poisson integral of U.
    ‚ąÉ (Z : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí (Fin d ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ))
      (h_Z_meas : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d,
        Measurable (Function.uncurry (fun ŌČ s => Z s ŌČ i)))
